column2: Clear skies- parly cloudy and calm.  Severe storm with 60+ MPH winds and 1.4 inches of rain on the evening of 7/27/10.  Water murkier and higher. Found 2 strands of EWM on SE shoreline by creek on 7/24 and 7/26.  Found more floating EWM (roots and lower half dead or dying and tops healthy) on 7/30 and found one established plant on NW shore of south bay. Will report to board and have it mapped for future reference. This was a treated area in May.
Hot- muggy- breezy day- partly cloudy. Lots of floating plant debris- algae bloom noted.
Weather cool- light breeze and overcast. Water dark- but clear.  Thunderstorms on the day before (6/21/11) with high winds and 2.2" of rain. Lake level up quite a bit.
Water somewhat murky- but a beautiful day!  Upper 70's- blue sky- light breeze.

column1: Great day to be on the water!

column2: Breezy- sunny- mid-40's. Ice out on 3/21/12!  Earliest anyone can remember. Crazy to have the boat in the water so soon.

Near 80 degrees- partly cloudy.  Matting areas of EWM in several places.
Sunny- breezy- lots of pollen in air and on water surface- upper 60's.
